Saturday, Feb. 14, 2015

Dear Friends and Neighbors
You are cordially invited to attend the 19th Annual BRISTOL FUN DAY Celebration & 11th Annual Antique Car & Tractor Show, which will be held on Sunday June 14th, 2015 at Levi Corser Park in Bristol Center, NY.
Every year Fun Day in Bristol is held to raise much-needed funds for the upkeep of Levi Corser Park & the Bristol Library. We do this by holding raffles and a silent auction in the Park Pavilion during Fun Day. Some items are donated by local Businesses, Craftsmen & Artisans, Musicians and Outreach Programs while others prefer to make a cash donation.
This year we would encourage anyone who would like donate to the silent auctions or raffles to drop off their donation at the town hall or to call Tom Stevens (585.919.0421) to arrange to have someone pick up your donation by May 28th. We can't thank those that have donated over the years for their support and hope you, too, will be part of BRISTOL FUN DAY this year.
We are hoping to follow the same schedule this year with the 10 am Service @ The Bristol Historical Society on Rt 64, 11 am the raffles, artists & craftsmen, vendors & auctions will open in the park. 11 am is also the time to get registered for the 11th Annual Antique Car & Vintage Tractor Show  which is looking to be bigger than ever with motorcycles, cars, trucks, & tractors of any shape and size welcomed.  At noon, the Fireman's chicken barbecue should be ready and at 3:00 pm  will be our annual Flag Retirement Ceremony by Boy Scout Troop 55. This is just the beginning and with your help there will be much more. 
As usual, we are still looking for volunteers so let us know if you would like to help out in the planning and execution of all this FUN! 
Anyone making a donation valued at $25.00 or more is also entitled to a 10'x10' or 10'x20' space to promote themselves and their business. In the past, besides local Artists' & Crafts(wo)men we have welcomed the Canandaigua VA, Habitat for Humanity, Cornell Co-op and many more.
If you are interested in making a donation and having a booth please return the information below.
o  I/we would like to make a donation to Bristol Fun Day - I/we will drop off a donation at the Bristol Town Hall by May 28th.  All monetary donations should be made out to The TOWN OF BRISTOL.
o  I/we would like someone to pick up the donation 
o  I/we would like a space to promote our business
PLEASE SEND THE FOLLOWING INFORMATION TO bristolfunday@gmail.com or snail mail to 7021 Rt 20A Bristol, NY 14469 ATTN: L Waden. All monetary donations should be made out to The TOWN OF BRISTOL

When I was working for my former employer, I took out a life insurance policy.When NY Life offered these policies to the employees, they said it made no difference what your previous medical history was. I questioned this on more than 4 occasions before signing up, not sharing to get into a policy and then have wasted my money. I have a history of severe COPD. Shortly  buying the policy, I was diagnosed with breast cancer. I have not been able to return to work due to complications. According to my polo y, I have a rider that says if I am disabled, NY Life will pay the remainder of my policy payments the rest of my life. I did not find this out until I had already been disabled for a year. So my agent told my they would retro pay me the policy payments I had already made, and then pay the rest. That was until the big wig New Yorkers got a hold of it and found out they might have to pay out a rider. So they have denied paying me, because 2 months before I bought the policy, I was in the hospital. But I thought that didn't matter? OH NO. They will find anything in the fine print to justify not paying a policy.  So here I am, a disabled widow, on Social Security Disability, which isn't much, and they prey on the people who they think won't fight back. Well, I would just like you, John Q Public, to know what kind of insurance trap NY Life is.
